Remember a user of your API can still pass Object[] for args. The varargs is just syntactic sugar. So a caller could call append("format...", new Object[]{a1,a2}) (your code will be safe here) or sadly they could call append("format ...", null); which I think will cause a NPE here.   If you truly want to guard this code consider adding a null check on args. 
   
String text = (args != null && args.length > 0) ? String.format(format, args) : format;

